{"type": "article", "id": 62444, "title": "卵石主题的卫浴产品，美得很克制｜这个设计了不起", "description": "我们每天都为你推荐几个最近发现的好设计。", "date": "2019-03-27T23:15:45Z", "super_tag": "", "tags": [{"id": 271, "name": "工业设计"}, {"id": 768, "name": "产品设计"}, {"id": 57528, "name": "Baker + Hesseldenz Studio"}, {"id": 57529, "name": "Artefatto"}, {"id": 57530, "name": "Sola Cube"}, {"id": 264, "name": "MUJI"}, {"id": 57531, "name": "D Line"}, {"id": 18745, "name": "Bjarke Ingels Group"}, {"id": 57532, "name": "Koichi Yoshimura"}], "category": 17, "column": 38, "author": 1329, "comment_count": 7, "praise_count": 157, "image": "img/article/article_show/20190327221629Ns4Xk8JVKI0aq1ju.jpg", "contents": "<p nocleanhtml=\"true\">        <style type=\"text/css\"> p.p1 {margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font: 11.0px Helvetica; color: #000000; -webkit-text-stroke: #000000} p.p2 {margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font: 11.0px 'PingFang SC'; color: #000000; -webkit-text-stroke: #000000} span.s1 {font-kerning: none} span.s2 {font: 11.0px Helvetica; font-kerning: none} span.s3 {text-decoration: underline ; font-kerning: none} span.s4 {font: 11.0px 'PingFang SC'; font-kerning: none} </style>  </p><h3>Pebble Collection by D Line</h3><p>最近，丹麦设计品牌 D Line 与 Bjarke Ingels Group 的特别项目部门 BIG IDEAS 合作，推出了 Pebble 系列新品，试图为无处不在的日常用品赋予奢华和高品质设计的质感。</p><p>整个系列呈鹅卵石状，俏皮又现代，包括皂液器、淋浴架、毛巾架、马桶刷、卷纸架、衣帽钩、杠杆手柄等等，提供哑光黑，哑光白或不锈钢可供选择钢。值得一提的是，每件产品都是手工制作，使用 50％至 70％的再生钢制成。售价 200 丹麦克朗起，<a href=\"https://shop.dline.com/designere/bjarke-ingels-group/c-2080/\" rel=\"nofollow\">点击这里尝试购买</a>。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20190327221644sNrnGbiM18H7zm5c.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.000000\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20190327221644S4Ornd8GV2jyBX53.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.182448\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20190327221645BwjTtY65FVaG74eg.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.000000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20190327221645ILQ50floZhUTVgdk.jpeg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.749867\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20190327221645jklMa7Pr821ip4dS.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.000000\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n<figcaption class=\"\">图片来源：<a href=\"https://shop.dline.com/designere/bjarke-ingels-group/c-2080/\" rel=\"nofollow\">D Line</a></figcaption></figure></div><h3>MUJI hotel ginza</h3><p>东京银座的MUJI酒店下月开业，位于银座中心地带，内部装饰以木、石、土为中心，巧妙使用了 50 年前东京有轨电车的垫轨碎石与废船木材。</p><p>总共 79 间客房中，最紧凑的客房横宽仅有 2.1 米。在这细长房间内，配置了让旅途疲惫者身心彻底放松的元素。如设置了符合人体工学的床垫，触感柔软的浴巾，柔和温馨的照明等，营造了超乎寻常的舒适空间。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201903272218049vZohYxVkIe2UMjO.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.667188\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20190327221805Gr8tiBevmpRUNKMW.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.667188\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20190327221805pZLEgBrymnGsHfwU.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.667188\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20190327221805AlubBGwOa61npDrd.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666807\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20190327221809NUSbDifzkVMh83rQ.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.665138\" data-format=\"png\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/2019032722181056QJaPF0e3bY2Dji.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.663609\" data-format=\"png\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/2019032722181552jivaSp4lhKgTDt.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.667178\" data-format=\"png\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20190327221814U0aNEScAvFg1tDTR.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.665644\" data-format=\"png\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20190327221816x6eDuPdiwNj2I9zA.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.663594\" data-format=\"png\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20190327221817jTZq3dmfxY8SpBuA.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.667692\" data-format=\"png\">\r\n</figure></div><h3>Sola Cube </h3><p>2006 年，设计师 Koichi Yoshimura 在日本京都创立品牌 Sola Cube，尝试留住每种植物最优雅的一面，将各植物制作成透明立体的生命标本，让各位可以作为永久细赏之装置小物。</p><p>整个产品需要经过繁复的生产工序，才能达至精莹通透的效果。 Koichi Yoshimura 在世界各地搜罗最独特的植物品种，包括蒲公英、水杉木、薰衣草、星辰花、七彩菊、黄茴香等等，并在花卉最灿烂的状态下，利用液态丙烯酸将其硬化并制成透明小方块，然后再以持续数小时的高温处理，通过真空高压方法将方块中的多余气泡排出，最后经专属工匠进行打磨抛光处理，做成花卉魔方。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20190327221909fo3c1dY0wuyXiT2O.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666667\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20190327221911euFa0OqWkXfHT4yA.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666667\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20190327221909YHt8Zqx1JLR6WeoA.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666667\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20190327221911RXBL59cNgEzoCxJs.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666667\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20190327221911rdFXYOj7abMueZzh.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666667\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20190327221912iGc6Sew02XM3YrHO.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666667\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20190327221912vCrlsE1ydeM2gHBi.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666667\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20190327221912ik7eF6Lod8vgHtXP.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666667\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20190327221912mUiIGkCJgpLT0Bbt.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666667\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20190327221912AweuGjkZ36HzcTQU.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666667\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20190327221913aNIYVSjJstdwT3eg.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666667\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20190327221913tQnoP4LHeyEUwhVi.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666667\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><h3>Secolo collection by Artefatto</h3><p>2017 年，设计工作室 Artefatto 在米兰家具展上脱颖而出。近两年，简单和实验成为了 Artefatto 的标签，他们擅长通过纹理和形式来讲述设计故事，尝试探索新技术和制造的可能性。</p><p>今年 1 月，Artefatto 与 Grottaglie 工匠合作，在普利亚大学创立了一个陶瓷元素设计课程。3 月初，他们在罗马举办个展。4 月份，他们将在米兰家具展展示他们的 Secolo 新系列，你可以看到各种组合形式的作品出现，既有奢华的材料，也有精致的饰面。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20190327222106WMUXeyTnauK1D2cN.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.690123\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20190327222106Yr5jsRF6LUIBQncp.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.250617\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20190327222106TXnwpOiEKRo5PCuG.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.711111\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201903272221062W7m5YQ10zu6q4Sj.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.334568\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20190327222106o6wrPuWNQdTiBkKs.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.416049\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201903272221074pwoz7WN2CbsIklD.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.755556\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20190327222107d6CsBRPQp5LGSrzT.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.795062\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20190327222107xjyR23aiJEH7OZnP.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.690123\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n<figcaption class=\"\">图片来源：<a href=\"http://www.artefatto.co.uk/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Artefatto</a></figcaption></figure></div><h3>Dudley by Baker + Hesseldenz Studio</h3><p>20 世纪中期诞生了一批经典座椅，他们线条简洁优雅，节省空间，易存储。但是 Baker + Hesseldenz Studio 却本着优先考虑奢华而非实用性，舒适而非理想主义的原则，设计了一把名为 Dudley 的餐椅。</p><p>这是一把手工精心制作的餐椅，采用胡桃木制成，背部是青铜板条编织而成，并配有毛绒坐垫，即便是长达数小时的晚餐或是交谈久坐时间，也不会有任何不适。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20190327222323nNtRwEUpbr8lmo5f.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.333333\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20190327222324jTJaeIs2lDy9QPuA.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.749867\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images medium-insert-active\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201903272223244rf9c1ApWdesy2Mg.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.749867\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n<figcaption class=\"\">图片来源：Baker + Hesseldenz Studio</figcaption></figure></div>"}